VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:std::mem::transmute|core::mem::transmute|mem::transmute|mem::uninitialized|MaybeUninit::assume_init)\s*(?:<[^>]+>)?\s*\(
WHEN EXPR MISSING:// SAFETY:|// Safety:|bytemuck|pod_read_unaligned|std::mem::zeroed
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects high-risk memory conversion and uninitialized-memory patterns in Rust.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Unsafe Memory Reinterpretation or Uninitialized Data.
